cription":null}],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":1,"created_at":"2026-05-13T18:30:30Z","updated_at":"2026-05-13T19:02:57Z","closed_at":"2026-05-13T19:02:38Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","issue_field_values":[],"type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"### Extension ID\n\nreqnroll-bdd\n\n### Extension Name\n\nReqnroll BDD\n\n### Version\n\n1.0.0\n\n### Description\n\nAdds Reqnroll BDD planning, Gherkin generation, traceability, safe task injection, handoff, and verification to Spec Kit.\n\n### Author\n\nLoogaCY Studio\n\n### Repository URL\n\nhttps://github.com/LoogacyStudio/spec-kit-reqnroll-bdd\n\n### Download URL\n\nhttps://github.com/LoogacyStudio/spec-kit-reqnroll-bdd/archive/refs/tags/v1.0.0.zip\n\n### License\n\nMIT\n\n### Homepage (optional)\n\nhttps://github.com/LoogacyStudio/spec-kit-reqnroll-bdd\n\n### Documentation URL (optional)\n\nhttps://github.com/LoogacyStudio/spec-kit-reqnroll-bdd#readme\n\n### Changelog URL (optional)\n\nhttps://github.com/LoogacyStudio/spec-kit-reqnroll-bdd/blob/main/CHANGELOG.md\n\n### Required Spec Kit Version\n\n>=0.8.0\n\n### Required Tools (optional)\n\n```markdown\n- dotnet - optional; used only when verification runs .NET/Requnroll tests\n```\n\n### Number of Commands\n\n4\n\n### Number of Hooks (optional)\n\n1\n\n### Tags\n\nbdd, reqnroll, dotnet, gherkin, acceptance-testing\n\n### Key Features\n\n- Classifies Spec Kit acceptance criteria into BDD and non-BDD test recommendations.\n- Generates Reqnroll-compatible Gherkin `.feature` files.\n- Generates AC-to-scenario traceability reports.\n- Generates implementation handoff guidance for `/speckit.implement`.\n- Injects BDD implementation tasks through an optional `before_implement` hook.\n- Provides step definition skeleton guidance without full implementation logic.\n- Verifies BDD coverage, scenario traceability, Gherkin quality, architecture boundaries, and optional `dotnet test` execution.\n\n### Testing Checklist\n\n- [x] Extension installs successfully via download URL\n- [x] All commands execute without errors\n- [x] Documentation is complete and accurate\n- [x] No security vulnerabilities identified\n- [x] Tested on at least one real project\n\n### Submission Requirements\n\n- [x] Valid `extension.yml` manifest included\n- [x] README.md with installation and usage instructions\n- [x] LICENSE file included\n- [x] GitHub release created with version tag\n- [x] All command files exist and are properly formatted\n- [x] Extension ID follows naming conventions (lowercase-with-hyphens)\n\n### Testing Details\n\n**Tested on:**\n\n- Spec Kit project using the `reqnroll-bdd` extension\n- Extension version: v1.0.0\n- Repository: https://github.com/LoogacyStudio/spec-kit-reqnroll-bdd\n\n**Tested install path:**\n\n```bash\nspecify extension add reqnroll-bdd --from https://github.com/LoogacyStudio/spec-kit-reqnroll-bdd/archive/refs/tags/v1.0.0.zip\n```\n\n**Real project dogfood:**\n\n* Feature: `001-rpg-snake-mvp`\n* Purpose: Validate the full BDD workflow from acceptance criteria to Reqnroll tests and verification.\n\n**Dogfood flow tested:**\n\n1. Ran `/speckit.reqnroll-bdd.plan`.\n2. Generated `bdd-test-plan.md`.\n3. Ran `/speckit.reqnroll-bdd.generate`.\n4. Generated Reqnroll-compatible `.feature` files.\n5. Generated `bdd-traceability.md`.\n6. Generated `bdd-implementation-handoff.md`.\n7. Ran `/speckit.implement`.\n8. Confirmed the optional `before_implement` hook can trigger `/speckit.reqnroll-bdd.inject-tasks`.\n9. Confirmed injected task block is bounded and idempotent.\n10. Confirmed step definition skeleton guidance does not include full implementation logic.\n11. Ran `/speckit.reqnroll-bdd.verify`.\n12. Ran .NET / Reqnroll test execution.\n\n**Test result:**\n\n```text\ndotnet test RpgSnake.Game.slnx\n\nTotal: 18\nFailed: 0\nPassed: 18\nSkipped: 0\n```\n\n**Safe skip path tested:**\n\n* Feature: `003-beautify-html5`\n* This feature did not go through `/speckit.reqnroll-bdd.generate`.\n* It did not contain:\n\n  * `bdd-implementation-handoff.md`\n  * `bdd-traceability.md`\n\nExpected and confirmed behavior:\n\n1. `before_implement` attempts to trigger `/speckit.reqnroll-bdd.inject-tasks`.\n2. Missing BDD generate artifacts cause task injection to skip.\n3. `tasks.md` is not modified.\n4. `/speckit.implement` is not blocked.\n\n**Architecture safety checks:**\n\n* Generated `.feature` files avoid implementation terms such as:\n\n  * `Aggregate`\n  * `Repository`\n  * `DTO`\n  * `Handler`\n  * `Controller`\n  * `ViewModel`\n  * `Presenter`\n  * `Godot`\n  * `Node`\n  * `Label`\n  * `Button`\n  * `Signal`\n  * `SceneTree`\n* Step definition guidance uses Application-boundary binding.\n* The extension does not replace `/speckit.implement`.\n\n\n### Example Usage\n\n```markdown\nspecify extension add reqnroll-bdd --from https://github.com/LoogacyStudio/spec-kit-reqnroll-bdd/archive/refs/tags/v1.0.0.zip\n``\n\nRun the normal Spec Kit flow:\n\n\n/speckit.specify\n/speckit.plan\n/speckit.tasks\n\n\nRun the Reqnroll BDD flow:\n\n\n/speckit.reqnroll-bdd.plan\n/speckit.reqnroll-bdd.generate\n/speckit.implement\n/speckit.reqnroll-bdd.verify\n\n\nBefore `/speckit.implement`, the optional `before_implement` hook may trigger:\n\n\n/speckit.reqnroll-bdd.inject-tasks\n\n\nGenerated artifacts may include:\n\n\nspecs/{feature}/bdd-test-plan.md\nspecs/{feature}/bdd-traceability.md\nspecs/{feature}/bdd-implementation-handoff.md\nspecs/{feature}/bdd-verification.md\ntests/{Project}.AcceptanceTests/Features/*.feature\n\n\nTask injection adds a bounded block to `tasks.md` only when the required BDD artifacts exist:\n\n\n<!-- reqnroll-bdd:tasks:start -->\n\n## BDD Acceptance Test Tasks\n\n- [ ] BDD-003 Create step definition skeletons\n  - Boundary: Application\n  - Skeleton only: `[Binding]`, constructor dependencies, Given/When/Then method signatures, and `PendingStepException`.\n\n- [ ] BDD-004 Complete step definitions through the Application boundary\n\n<!-- reqnroll-bdd:tasks:end -->\n```\n\n### Proposed Catalog Entry\n\n```json\n{\n  \"reqnroll-bdd\": {\n    \"name\": \"Reqnroll BDD\",\n    \"id\": \"reqnroll-bdd\",\n    \"description\": \"Adds Reqnroll BDD planning, Gherkin generation, traceability, safe task injection, handoff, and verification to Spec Kit.\",\n    \"author\": \"LoogaCY Studio\",\n    \"version\": \"1.0.0\",\n    \"download_url\": \"https://github.com/LoogacyStudio/spec-kit-reqnroll-bdd/archive/refs/tags/v1.0.0.zip\",\n    \"repository\": \"https://github.com/LoogacyStudio/spec-kit-reqnroll-bdd\",\n    \"homepage\": \"https://github.com/LoogacyStudio/spec-kit-reqnroll-bdd\",\n    \"documentation\": \"https://github.com/LoogacyStudio/spec-kit-reqnroll-bdd#readme\",\n    \"changelog\": \"https://github.com/LoogacyStudio/spec-kit-reqnroll-bdd/blob/main/CHANGELOG.md\",\n    \"license\": \"MIT\",\n    \"requires\": {\n      \"speckit_version\": \">=0.8.0\",\n      \"tools\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"dotnet\",\n          \"required\": false\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    \"provides\": {\n      \"commands\": 4,\n      \"hooks\": 1\n    },\n    \"tags\": [\n      \"bdd\",\n      \"reqnroll\",\n      \"dotnet\",\n      \"gherkin\",\n      \"acceptance-testing\"\n    ],\n    \"verified\": false,\n    \"downloads\": 0,\n    \"stars\": 0,\n    \"created_at\": \"2026-05-14T00:00:00Z\",\n    \"updated_at\": \"2026-05-14T00:00:00Z\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### Additional Context\n\nThis extension is intentionally scoped to BDD preparation and verification.\n\nIt does not replace `/speckit.implement`; instead, it prepares BDD artifacts and safe implementation guidance for the native Spec Kit implementation flow.\n\nKey design boundaries:\n\n- `.feature` files must remain implementation-agnostic.\n- Step definitions should bind through Application Services or test-facing Application facades.\n- Task injection is optional, idempotent, and safely skipped when BDD generate artifacts are missing.\n- Step definition skeleton guidance is incomplete by design and must not include full business logic.\n- `dotnet` is optional and only used when verification runs .NET / Reqnroll tests.\n\nThe extension has been dogfooded on a real Spec Kit feature and includes a safe skip path for features that do not use the Reqnroll BDD generate flow.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/github/spec-kit/issues/2544/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/github/spec-kit/issues/2544/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/npmx-dev/npmx.dev/issues/2719","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/npmx-dev/npmx.dev","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/npmx-dev/npmx.dev/issues/2719/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/npmx-dev/npmx.dev/issues/2719/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/npmx-dev/npmx.dev/issues/2719/events","html_url":"https://github.com/npmx-dev/npmx.dev/issues/2719","id":4424279397,"node_id":"I_kwDOQ_ILBs8AAAABB7UlZQ","number":2719,"title":"Org tooltip in package name is hidden behind package subheader","user":{"login":"mootari","id":322014,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjMyMjAxNA==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/322014?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/mootari","html_url":"https://github.com/mootari","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mootari/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mootari/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mootari/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mootari/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions