0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"Two structural issues that bit us tonight:\n\n## 1. Version-slot races with parallel agents\n\nMy session's planned v0.3.1 collided with a parallel session's v0.3.1 (same tag, different scope). Caught only by `gh release list` — not by `scripts/release-kit.sh`, which checks local tags but not origin.\n\n**Fix**: `release-kit.sh` does `git fetch origin --tags --quiet` and aborts if the proposed tag exists on origin. ~5 lines.\n\n## 2. Doc pins go stale every release\n\nPR #260 bumped 5 files from `kit-v0.3.x` → `kit-v0.4.0`. We'll do this again on every release.\n\n**Fix**: workflow copies the tarball to a stable filename `subconscious-ai-kit.tgz` and attaches BOTH the versioned and the stable-name asset to each release. Docs default to the `releases/latest/download/subconscious-ai-kit.tgz` URL (auto-redirects to the latest release's stable-name asset). Pinned-version URL still works for consumers who want to pin.\n\n`kit-release.yml` change is ~3 lines (`cp` + extra arg to `gh release create`).\n\nDocs change: 5 files, default to latest-URL, document pinned-URL as alternative.\n\n## Acceptance\n\n- [ ] `release-kit.sh` aborts cleanly when proposed tag exists on origin (`git tag -a kit-v0.4.0` while v0.4.0 already exists → exit 1 with message)\n- [ ] kit-v0.4.1 release artifact has BOTH `subconscious-ai-kit-0.4.1.tgz` AND `subconscious-ai-kit.tgz`\n- [ ] `pnpm add 'https://github.com/Subconscious-ai/design-system/releases/latest/download/subconscious-ai-kit.tgz'` in scratch repo resolves to the latest version\n- [ ] Docs default to the latest-URL; the v0.4.1 release ships v0.4.1 + the latest alias\n\n## Out of scope\n\nNo kit code changes — this is purely release infrastructure.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Subconscious-ai/design-system/issues/262/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket