ssociation":"NONE","active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"\n\n## Summary\n\nI tried reading the \"skill-only\" setup as if I were a new user, and the current docs really oversell how self-contained it is.\n\nThe README says I can basically copy `skill/`, `chmod +x` the scripts, point a couple env vars at the backend, and go. But the scripts themselves still depend on things that are never installed or declared anywhere.\n\nSo the advertised quick-start is not actually a clean quick-start.\n\n## Affected files\n\n- `README.md`\n- `skill/SKILL.md`\n- `skill/scripts/crwlr`\n- `skill/scripts/cdp-download`\n\n## Current behavior\n\nThe docs currently suggest this is enough:\n\n```bash\ngit clone https://github.com/huangyrcn/web-kit.git\ncp -r web-kit/skill ~/.claude/skills/web-kit\nchmod +x ~/.claude/skills/web-kit/scripts/*\n```\n\nBut in practice:\n\n- `scripts/crwlr` shells out to `crwl`\n- `scripts/cdp-download` imports Python `websocket`\n- there is no dependency manifest in the repo telling users what to install\n- the docs do not clearly mention these extra runtime requirements\n\nSo on a clean machine, first-run failures like these seem pretty likely:\n\n- `crwl: command not found`\n- `ModuleNotFoundError: No module named 'websocket'`\n\n## Expected behavior\n\nEither:\n- the skill-only path should actually work on a clean environment, or\n- the docs should be very explicit that users still need to install extra runtime dependencies\n\nRight now it's kind of in the worst middle ground: looks simple, fails late.\n\n## Suggested fixes\n\n1. Add a dependency manifest for the skill scripts.\n2. Document required runtime dependencies in one obvious place.\n3. Add a simple self-check / doctor command.\n4. Fail earlier with a friendlier message when `crwl` or `websocket-client` is missing.\n\n## Why this matters\n\nThis is not just a docs polish issue. It directly affects the first-run experience for one of the repo's main selling points.\n\nIf the first thing a user hits is \"command not found\", that undercuts the whole lightweight-skill story pretty quickly.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/huangyrcn/web-kit/issues/4/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/huangyrcn/web-kit/issues/4/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/1amageek/database-framework/issues/4","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/1amageek/database-framework","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/1amageek/database-framework/issues/4/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/1amageek/database-framework/issues/4/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/1amageek/database-framework/issues/4/events","html_url":"https://github.com/1amageek/database-framework/issues/4","id":4435707280,"node_id":"I_kwDOQgKqOM8AAAABCGOFkA","number":4,"title":"Handle retryable StorageError conflicts as transaction retries","user":{"login":"1amageek","id":11146538,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjExMTQ2NTM4","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/11146538?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/1amageek","html_url":"https://github.com/1amageek","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/1amageek/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/1amageek/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/1amageek/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/1amageek/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/1amageek/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/1amageek/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/1amageek/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/1amageek/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/1amageek/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":1,"created_at":"2026-05-13T07:10:38Z","updated_at":"2026-05-19T01:34:28Z","closed_at":"2026-05-19T01:34:28Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"OWNER","active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"## Problem\n\nAURORA observed a user-facing save failure while writing Memory data through the SQLite-backed database stack:\n\n```text\nSave to Memory failed: The operation couldn’t be completed. (StorageKit.StorageError error 1.)\n```\n\nThe same operation log later showed the MCP `store` call succeeded:\n\n```text\n[MemoryMCP] [MCP] store: decoded 28 entities, 25 statements\n[MemoryMCP] [MCP] store: success\n[MemoryMCP] [MCP] store result: isError=false\n```\n\n`StorageError error 1` appears to correspond to `StorageError.transactionTooOld`, which is retryable. When this is eventually recovered, surfacing it as a final user-facing error is misleading.\n\n## Expected behavior\n\nRetryable storage conflicts should be handled below application UI code:\n\n- `StorageError.transactionTooOld` and `StorageError.transactionConflict` should be retried by the transaction runner when possible.\n- If retry eventually succeeds, the condition should be logged as debug/warning only, not propagated as a final error.\n- If retries are exhausted, the operation should throw a meaningful final error.\n- `StorageError` should provide useful descriptions instead of the opaque Foundation fallback: `StorageKit.StorageError error 1`.\n\n## Why this matters\n\nAURORA supports multiple concurrent research jobs. Research can run in parallel, but Memory writes may overlap against the same SQLite-backed database. The application can serialize writes as a workaround, but the database layer should still provide correct retry semantics and clear error reporting for retryable conflicts.\n\n## Suggested design\n\n```mermaid\nflowchart TD\n  A[Storage transaction] --> B{StorageError.isRetryable?}\n  B -->|yes| C[Retry with backoff]\n  C --> D{Success?}\n  D -->|yes| E[Return success, log warning/debug]\n  D -->|no, exhausted| F[Throw final descriptive error]\n  B -->|no| G[Throw immediately]\n```\n\nImplementation considerations:\n\n- Add or verify retry policy in the database-framework transaction execution path for retryable `StorageError` values.\n- Keep retry boundaries around DB work only; callers should not need to rerun expensive pre-processing such as entity extraction or embedding generation.\n- Add `LocalizedError` / `CustomStringConvertible` conformance for `StorageError` so diagnostics identify the actual case and message.\n- Add tests for SQLite transaction conflict / transaction-too-old behavior where practical.\n\n## Current workaround in AURORA\n\nAURORA now serializes Memory store operations with a per-runner write gate to reduce concurrent writer conflicts. This should not be considered the complete fix; database-framework should still retry retryable transaction errors and expose descriptive failures.\n","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/1amageek/database-framework/issues/4/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/1amageek/database-framework/issues/4/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/binsarjr/sveltego/issues/26","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/binsarjr/sveltego","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/binsarjr/sveltego/issues/26/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/binsarjr/sveltego/issues/26/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/binsarjr/sveltego/issues/26/events","html_url":"https://github.com/binsarjr/sveltego/issues/26","id":4346319024,"node_id":"I_kwDOSPSdXM8AAAABAw-QsA","number":26,"title":"Hooks: hooks.server.go Handle middleware chain","user":{"login":"binsarjr","id":33781288,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjMzNzgxMjg4","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/33781288?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/binsarjr","html_url":"https://github.com/binsarjr","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/binsarjr/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/binsarjr/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/binsarjr/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/binsarjr/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/binsarjr/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/binsarjr/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/binsarjr/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/binsarjr/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/binsarjr/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[{"id":10815273849,"node_id":"LA_kwDOSPSdXM8AAAAChKP7eQ","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/binsarjr/sveltego/labels/area:hooks","name":"area:hooks","color":"d4c5f9","default":false,"description":"handle, handleError, handleFetch"},{"id":10815274207,"node_id":"LA_kwDOSPSdXM8AAAAChKP83w","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/binsarjr/sveltego/labels/type:feature","name":"type:feature","color":"a2eeef","default":false,"description":"New capability"},{"id":10815274503,"node_id":"LA_kwDOSPSdXM8AAAAChKP-Bw","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/binsarjr/sveltego/labels/priority:p1","name":"priority:p1","color":"d93f0b","default":false,"description":"Important"}],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/binsarjr/sveltego/milestones/2","html_url":"https://github.com/binsarjr/sveltego/milestone/2","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/binsarjr/sveltego/milestones/2/labels","id":15720965,"node_id":"MI_kwDOSPSdXM4A7-IF","number":2,"title":"v0.2 — Form Actions & Hooks","description":"Form actions, hooks chain, error boundary, +server.go.","creator":{"login":"binsarjr","id":33781288,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjMzNzgxMjg4","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/33781288?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/binsarjr","html_url":"https://github.com/binsarjr","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/binsarjr/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/binsarjr/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/binsarjr/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/binsarjr/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/binsarjr/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/binsarjr/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/binsarjr/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/binsarjr/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/binsarjr/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"open_issues":0,"closed_issues":15,"state":"open","created_at":"2026-04-28T21:18:54Z","updated_at":"2026-04-30T08:59:15Z","due_on":"2026-08-31T00:00:00Z","closed_at":null},"comments":0,"created_at":"2026-04-28T21:24:00Z","updated_at":"2026-04-30T06:04:08Z","closed_at":"2026-04-30T06:04:08Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"OWNER","active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"## Summary\n\nImplement the `Handle` middleware chain in `src/hooks.server.go`, allowing global request rewriting, auth, logging, and short-circuit responses before the route handler runs.\n\n## Background\n\nSvelteKit's `handle({ event, resolve })` is the single global hook every request flows through. sveltego must expose the equivalent so projects can attach session loading, CORS headers, request IDs, rate limiting — all in one place. The shape must allow chaining (multiple hooks composed via `kit.Sequence`).\n\n## Goals\n\n- [ ] Discover `src/hooks.server.go` and detect a top-level `Handle` symbol.\n- [ ] Codegen wires `Handle` around the route resolver in the HTTP pipeline.\n- [ ] `kit.Sequence(h1, h2, h3)` composes multiple handles left-to-right.\n- [ ] Hook can short-circuit by returning a response without calling `resolve`.\n\n## Non-Goals\n\n- `HandleError` / `HandleFetch` — covered in #27.\n- Hot reload of hooks during dev — covered in #42.\n\n## Detailed Design\n\nSignature:\n\n```go\npackage hooks\n\nimport \"github.com/binsarjr/sveltego/kit\"\n\nfunc Handle(ev *kit.RequestEvent, resolve kit.ResolveFn) (*kit.Response, error) {\n    ev.Locals.Set(\"requestID\", uuid.NewString())\n    if user, ok := loadSession(ev); ok {\n        ev.Locals.Set(\"user\", user)\n    }\n    res, err := resolve(ev)\n    if err != nil { return nil, err }\n    res.Headers.Set(\"X-Request-ID\", ev.Locals.GetString(\"requestID\"))\n    return res, nil\n}\n```\n\nPipeline orchestration:\n\n```go\n// .gen/server/main.go\nfunc ServeHTTP(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n    ev := kit.NewRequestEvent(r)\n    resolve := func(ev *kit.RequestEvent) (*kit.Response, error) {\n        return router.Resolve(ev) // route lookup + Load + Render\n    }\n    res, err := hooks.Handle(ev, resolve)\n    // emit response\n}\n```\n\n`kit.Sequence`:\n\n```go\nfunc Sequence(handlers ...HandleFn) HandleFn {\n    return func(ev *RequestEvent, resolve ResolveFn) (*Response, error) {\n        next := resolve\n        for i := len(handlers)-1; i >= 0; i-- {\n            h, n := handlers[i], next\n            next = func(ev *RequestEvent) (*Response, error) { return h(ev, n) }\n        }\n        return next(ev)\n    }\n}\n```\n\nDiscovery: parser reads `src/hooks.server.go` via `go/ast`, verifies `Handle` exists and matches the expected signature, otherwise emits a no-op.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Project with one Handle adds a header observable in the HTTP response.\n- [ ] `kit.Sequence(a, b)` calls a, then b, then route resolver in that order.\n- [ ] Short-circuit (returning a response without calling resolve) skips the route.\n- [ ] Missing `hooks.server.go` works — codegen emits identity handler.\n- [ ] Hook errors propagate to `HandleError` (#27).\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n- Unit: `kit.Sequence` ordering, short-circuit, error propagation.\n- Integration: HTTP test asserts header set by hook present, asserts short-circuit returns without invoking route.\n- Golden: emitted pipeline file with and without `hooks.server.go`.\n\n## Out of Scope\n\n- `transformPageChunk` (HTML stream rewriting) — defer to v0.4.\n- Filter (which routes a hook applies to) — currently global.\n\n## Risks & Open Questions\n\n- Closure allocation in `Sequence` — benchmark and inline if hot.\n- Authors using globals to share state across requests — document Locals as the canonical store.\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- Blocks: #27 (HandleError observes hook errors), #30 (form actions need locals).\n- Blocked by: #17 (Locals), #20 (HTTP pipeline).\n\n## References\n\n- SvelteKit hooks: https://kit.svelte.dev/docs/hooks#server-hooks-handle\n","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/binsarjr/sveltego/issues/26/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/binsarjr/sveltego/issues/26/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rickbeeloo/barbell/issues/24","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rickbeeloo/barbell","labels_