sely)\n\nBut encountered many reads dropped at `filter` step\n=> Only about 1/3 reads left (compared to `dorado` output)\n\nAfter `barbell inspect` I understand my top seen pattern is **not included** by `barbell kit`: `Ftag[fw, *, @left(0..250)]__Ftag[rc, *, @right(0..250)]`\n=> Using `seqkit locate`, I could confirm that reads with this pattern actually show **same barcode**, but :\n* Once at begining of read\n* A 2nd time reverse-complemented at the end of read\n<br>\n\nCould you provide any guidelines please ?\n=> Is there something wrong with my data ?\n=> This is WGS of Human (protocol for PromethION)\n\nI know I could include this pattern and re-run from `filter` step, but I would first like to understand why I loose so many reads using `barbell kit`\n<br>\n\nThanks for your help !\nBest,\nFelix.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rickbeeloo/barbell/issues/24/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rickbeeloo/barbell/issues/24/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/joshuafolkken/game-kit/issues/135","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/joshuafolkken/game-kit","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/joshuafolkken/game-kit/issues/135/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/joshuafolkken/game-kit/issues/135/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/joshuafolkken/game-kit/issues/135/events","html_url":"https://github.com/joshuafolkken/game-kit/issues/135","id":4505349103,"node_id":"I_kwDOST2KUM8AAAABDIor7w","number":135,"title":"jgame init hardcodes `vite preview`, and jgame sync does not keep the `preview` script in sync","user":{"login":"joshuafolkken","id":168330964,"node_id":"U_kgDOCgiG1A","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/168330964?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/joshuafolkken","html_url":"https://github.com/joshuafolkken","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joshuafolkken/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joshuafolkken/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joshuafolkken/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joshuafolkken/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joshuafolkken/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joshuafolkken/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joshuafolkken/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joshuafolkken/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joshuafolkken/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[{"id":10859572438,"node_id":"LA_kwDOST2KUM8AAAACh0fs1g","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/joshuafolkken/game-kit/labels/in-progress","name":"in-progress","color":"0075ca","default":false,"description":"Work is actively in progress"}],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":2,"created_at":"2026-05-22T20:10:48Z","updated_at":"2026-05-22T20:30:02Z","closed_at":"2026-05-22T20:30:00Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"OWNER","active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"## Background\n\n`@joshuafolkken/game-kit` and every project it initialises (e.g. `joshuafolkken/mnemecha`) use the `@sveltejs/adapter-cloudflare` adapter. To exercise the Cloudflare Worker runtime locally and during CI E2E (so `hooks.server.ts` security headers, redirects, and HTML-template injection actually execute), the `preview` script must run the Worker — `vite preview` only serves static assets and bypasses the Worker entirely.\n\n`@joshuafolkken/game-kit` itself uses the right script:\n\n```json\n\"preview\": \"wrangler dev .svelte-kit/cloudflare/_worker.js --port 4173\"\n```\n\n## Problem\n\nThere are two related sync gaps:\n\n1. **`jgame init` hardcodes `vite preview`** in the generated `package.json`. See `dist/scripts/jgame.js` (the bundled init template literal, around the `preview:` entry). New projects initialised via `jgame init` ship the wrong preview command and silently fail CI E2E coverage that depends on the Worker runtime (e.g. CSP headers, SW registration, hostname redirect).\n\n2. **`jgame sync` does not manage `package.json` scripts.** Today the sync covers `.npmrc`, `src/app.d.ts`, `src/app.html`, `src/hooks.server.ts`, `src/routes/+layout.svelte`, `src/routes/layout.css`, `svelte.config.js`, and `vite.config.ts`. Even if (1) is fixed in the init template, existing projects that already have `\"preview\": \"vite preview\"` from a prior `jgame init` are never corrected by `pnpm jgame sync` — they keep silently drifting from game-kit's own behaviour.\n\nConcretely surfaced in `joshuafolkken/mnemecha#252`: after migrating that project to consume `@joshuafolkken/game-kit`, the local pre-push E2E hook (which runs in CI mode = build + preview) failed all 27 tests with `ERR_CONNECTION_REFUSED` until the `preview` script was manually corrected to match game-kit's own.\n\n## Expected outcome\n\n- `jgame init` writes `\"preview\": \"wrangler dev .svelte-kit/cloudflare/_worker.js --port 4173\"` (matching game-kit's own `package.json#scripts.preview`) into the new project's `package.json`.\n- `jgame sync` (or the underlying `josh sync` it delegates to) detects a stale `preview` script in the consumer's `package.json` and corrects it, matching the canonical value from game-kit. Other `package.json` script keys that are part of the kit-managed contract should be considered for the same treatment (scoped narrowly — do not blanket-overwrite consumer-owned scripts).\n- The fix is verifiable end-to-end: a freshly-initialised `jgame init` project, run with `CI=1 pnpm exec playwright test --workers=2`, brings up the Worker runtime on port 4173 and passes every E2E that exercises `hooks.server.ts`.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- [ ] `dist/scripts/jgame.js` (and the source it is built from under `src/lib/scripts/jgame-init`) writes the canonical `preview` script during `jgame init`.\n- [ ] `jgame sync` enforces the canonical `preview` script on existing projects (either by adding a `package.json` script-key sync pass in `jgame-sync.ts`, or by extending `josh sync` to cover the same key — implementer's call, see Plan).\n- [ ] The canonical value lives in one place (a single source of truth that both `jgame init` and `jgame sync` read from) so the two paths cannot drift in future kit releases.\n- [ ] Unit test in game-kit covers the script value emitted by `jgame init` and the corrective behaviour of `jgame sync`.\n- [ ] Manual: `jgame init test-app && cd test-app && CI=1 pnpm exec playwright test` — Worker-runtime-dependent tests pass.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/joshuafolkken/game-kit/issues/135/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/joshuafolkken/game-kit/issues/135/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sveltejs/kit/issues/15855","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sveltejs/kit","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sveltejs/kit/issues/15855/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sveltejs/kit/issues/15855/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sveltejs/kit/issues/15855/events","html_url":"https://github.com/sveltejs/kit/issues/15855","id":4459265770,"node_id":"I_kwDOEiPr8c8AAAABCcr-6g","number":15855,"title":"docs: modules in service workers is now baseline","user":{"login":"hyunbinseo","id":47051820,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjQ3MDUxODIw"