vatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/binsarjr","html_url":"https://github.com/binsarjr","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/binsarjr/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/binsarjr/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/binsarjr/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/binsarjr/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/binsarjr/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/binsarjr/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/binsarjr/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/binsarjr/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/binsarjr/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"open_issues":4,"closed_issues":59,"state":"open","created_at":"2026-04-28T21:18:57Z","updated_at":"2026-05-03T15:18:37Z","due_on":"2027-02-28T00:00:00Z","closed_at":null},"comments":0,"created_at":"2026-04-28T21:25:46Z","updated_at":"2026-04-30T10:15:26Z","closed_at":"2026-04-30T10:15:26Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"OWNER","active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"## Summary\n\nBuild a non-trivial blog example app under `examples/blog/` demonstrating routing, dynamic params, layouts, form actions (comments), markdown rendering via `{@html}`, and pagination.\n\n## Background\n\nTutorial-grade examples are the highest-leverage docs. A blog covers ~80% of features in a familiar shape.\n\n## Goals\n\n- [ ] Pages: index (paginated list), post detail, tag list, about.\n- [ ] Layouts: root + section-level.\n- [ ] Posts stored as Markdown files (`content/posts/*.md`); compiled via `goldmark`.\n- [ ] Comment form using `Actions()` and form binding.\n- [ ] Search input that prefetches results from `/api/search/__data.json`.\n- [ ] Deployed example URL referenced in docs.\n\n## Non-Goals\n\n- Full CMS / admin panel.\n- Authentication.\n\n## Detailed Design\n\nTree:\n\n```\nexamples/blog/\n  src/\n    routes/\n      +layout.svelte\n      +layout.server.go              ← loads site config\n      +page.svelte                   ← index list\n      +page.server.go\n      blog/[slug]/+page.svelte\n      blog/[slug]/+page.server.go\n      tag/[tag]/+page.svelte\n      tag/[tag]/+page.server.go\n      api/search/+server.go\n    content/\n      posts/*.md\n    lib/\n      md/render.go\n  static/\n    favicon.svg\n  go.mod\n```\n\nMarkdown render helper:\n\n```go\n// lib/md/render.go\nfunc Render(src []byte) (template.HTML, error) {\n    var buf bytes.Buffer\n    if err := goldmark.Convert(src, &buf); err != nil { return \"\", err }\n    return template.HTML(buf.String()), nil\n}\n```\n\nComment action:\n\n```go\nvar Actions = kit.ActionMap{\n    \"default\": func(ev *kit.RequestEvent) kit.ActionResult {\n        var c CommentForm\n        ev.BindForm(&c)\n        if c.Body == \"\" { return kit.ActionFail(400, c) }\n        appendComment(ev.Params[\"slug\"], c)\n        return kit.ActionRedirect(303, ev.URL.Path)\n    },\n}\n```\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] All listed pages render via `sveltego dev`.\n- [ ] Markdown-to-HTML uses sanitizer (`bluemonday`) to ensure safe `{@html}`.\n- [ ] Pagination works (prev/next).\n- [ ] Comment form submits and re-renders with new comment.\n- [ ] Search box does prefetch + SPA navigation.\n- [ ] README in `examples/blog/` documents how to run.\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n- Smoke: `sveltego build` succeeds.\n- Playwright: navigate index → post → submit comment → see it.\n\n## Out of Scope\n\n- DB persistence (in-memory or filesystem only).\n\n## Risks & Open Questions\n\n- Markdown rendering performance — cache compiled HTML on disk.\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- Blocks: docs site links to it.\n- Blocked by: #55, #59.\n\n## References\n\n- Goldmark: https://github.com/yuin/goldmark\n","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/binsarjr/sveltego/issues/62/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/binsarjr/sveltego/issues/62/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/binsarjr/sveltego/issues/23","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/binsarjr/sveltego","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/binsarjr/sveltego/issues/23/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/binsarjr/sveltego/issues/23/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/binsarjr/sveltego/issues/23/events","html_url":"https://github.com/binsarjr/sveltego/issues/23","id":4346318062,"node_id":"I_kwDOSPSdXM8AAAABAw-M7g","number":23,"title":"Example: hello-world app for smoke testing","user":{"login":"binsarjr","id":33781288,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjMzNzgxMjg4","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/33781288?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/binsarjr","html_url":"https://github.com/binsarjr","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/binsarjr/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/binsarjr/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/binsarjr/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/binsarjr/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/binsarjr/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/binsarjr/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/binsarjr/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/binsarjr/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/binsarjr/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[{"id":10815274023,"node_id":"LA_kwDOSPSdXM8AAAAChKP8Jw","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/binsarjr/sveltego/la