_at":"2026-04-30T05:12:58Z","due_on":"2026-07-14T00:00:00Z","closed_at":null},"comments":3,"created_at":"2026-04-28T21:23:51Z","updated_at":"2026-04-30T03:31:41Z","closed_at":"2026-04-30T03:31:04Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"OWNER","active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"## Summary\n\nA minimal example application under `examples/hello/` that exercises the full MVP pipeline: routing, load, render, response. Doubles as the smoke test in CI.\n\n## Background\n\nA failing example is the most public possible signal that a refactor broke something. We keep it minimal: one or two routes, no bells.\n\n## Goals\n\n- [ ] Example builds via `cd examples/hello && go run ./cmd/app` (or via `sveltego build`)\n- [ ] Two routes: `/` and `/post/[id]`\n- [ ] One layout\n- [ ] CI builds and curls both routes\n\n## Detailed Design\n\n### Structure\n\n```\nexamples/hello/\n├── go.mod                              # replace github.com/binsarjr/sveltego => ../..\n├── app.html\n├── src/\n│   └── routes/\n│       ├── +layout.svelte\n│       ├── +page.svelte\n│       ├── +page.server.go\n│       └── post/\n│           └── [id]/\n│               ├── +page.svelte\n│               └── +page.server.go\n└── cmd/\n    └── app/\n        └── main.go\n```\n\n### `+page.server.go` (root)\n\n```go\npackage root\n\nimport \"github.com/binsarjr/sveltego/pkg/kit\"\n\ntype PageData struct {\n    Greeting string\n    Posts    []Post\n}\n\ntype Post struct {\n    ID    string\n    Title string\n}\n\nfunc Load(ctx *kit.LoadCtx) (PageData, error) {\n    return PageData{\n        Greeting: \"Hello, sveltego!\",\n        Posts: []Post{\n            {ID: \"1\", Title: \"First post\"},\n            {ID: \"2\", Title: \"Second post\"},\n        },\n    }, nil\n}\n```\n\n### `+page.svelte` (root)\n\n```svelte\n<script lang=\"go\"></script>\n\n<h1>{data.Greeting}</h1>\n\n{#if len(data.Posts) > 0}\n  <ul>\n    {#each data.Posts as p}\n      <li><a href=\"/post/{p.ID}\">{p.Title}</a></li>\n    {/each}\n  </ul>\n{:else}\n  <p>No posts.</p>\n{/if}\n```\n\n### `+page.server.go` (post/[id])\n\n```go\npackage post_id\n\nimport (\n    \"errors\"\n    \"github.com/binsarjr/sveltego/pkg/kit\"\n)\n\ntype PageData struct {\n    Title string\n    Body  string\n}\n\nfunc Load(ctx *kit.LoadCtx) (PageData, error) {\n    id := ctx.Params[\"id\"]\n    if id == \"\" {\n        return PageData{}, errors.New(\"missing id\")\n    }\n    return PageData{\n        Title: \"Post \" + id,\n        Body:  \"This is the body of post \" + id + \".\",\n    }, nil\n}\n```\n\n### `+page.svelte` (post/[id])\n\n```svelte\n<h1>{data.Title}</h1>\n<p>{data.Body}</p>\n<a href=\"/\">Back</a>\n```\n\n### `cmd/app/main.go`\n\n```go\npackage main\n\nimport (\n    \"log\"\n    \"github.com/binsarjr/sveltego/pkg/server\"\n    \"github.com/example/hello/.gen\"\n)\n\nfunc main() {\n    s := server.New(gen.Manifest)\n    log.Fatal(s.ListenAndServe(\":3000\"))\n}\n```\n\n### CI smoke\n\n```yaml\n- run: cd examples/hello && go run github.com/binsarjr/sveltego/cmd/sveltego build\n- run: examples/hello/build/app &\n- run: sleep 1 && curl -fsS http://localhost:3000/ | grep \"Hello, sveltego!\"\n- run: curl -fsS http://localhost:3000/post/123 | grep \"Post 123\"\n```\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Example builds\n- [ ] Both routes return expected HTML (verified via curl in CI)\n- [ ] README in `examples/hello/` explains how to run\n- [ ] No external dependencies (no DB, no third-party libs)\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n- CI smoke as documented.\n- Manual: `cd examples/hello && sveltego build && ./build/app`, then visit in browser.\n\n## Out of Scope\n\n- Production styling.\n- Hydration (deferred to v0.3).\n\n## Risks\n\n1. The `replace` directive in `go.mod` is required during dev; documented in README.\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- Blocked by: #5, #18, #20, #21.\