y":"## Context\n\nSurface'd in naschool repo (2026-05-23, sectie 3 domain-model session). User asked `/ai:which` for \"auditor die code reviewt obv design patterns, coding guidelines, best practices, dry, solid, yagni, naming conventions etc.\"\n\n`/ai:which` keyword-scoring returned 3 non-matches (`grill-me`, `prototype`, `recommend-tools`) because \"review/audit/quality\" are not in current skill descriptions strongly enough. Real candidates surfaced by manually scanning available skills:\n\n| Skill | Scope | Gap |\n|---|---|---|\n| `frontend-audit` (project-local in naschool) | `portal/` `admin/` `partner/` `web/` | exact-match: file-size hotspots, FSD-laag-violations, duplicatie, god-components, props-bloat, naming, tooltips, a11y. **Project-tuned — niet portable.** |\n| `/ai:review` | branch/diff | pre-merge code review tegen base-branch. **Diff-only — geen whole-codebase architectuur-audit.** |\n| `/audit` (slash-skill) | current code | generic, geen design-pattern of SOLID/DRY/YAGNI-systematiek |\n| `react-doctor` | React only | bundle/a11y/lint focus, niet design-patterns |\n| `simplify` | changed code | refactor-fix, schrijft code |\n| `caveman:cavecrew-reviewer` | diff/file | compressed-output review, geen architectuur-audit |\n\n## Gap\n\nGeen ai-kit-canonical skill voor: **whole-codebase architecture-quality audit** met expliciete dimensies:\n\n- Design patterns (Repository/Service/Policy/Factory/Strategy etc. — gebruikt waar passend, niet overal?)\n- SOLID violations (god-classes, single-responsibility, open-closed)\n- DRY (duplicatie-kandidaten, copy-paste blocks)\n- YAGNI (premature abstractions, unused branches, dead config)\n- Naming conventions (entity-naam-drift, abbreviation-mismatch, misleading names)\n- Layer/dependency-direction violations (architecture rules)\n- Coupling/cohesion smells (god-modules, feature-envy)\n\nFrontend-audit pattern in naschool toont dat dit *werkt* — maar moet per project opnieuw geschreven worden. ai-kit moet hier een **stack-agnostic foundation** voor leveren, met per-stack tuning-hooks.\n\n## Voorstel — 3 primitives\n\n**A. `audit-architecture` skill (ai-kit canonical)**\n- Trigger-detectie: \"audit code\", \"review this codebase\", \"check design patterns\", \"SOLID violations\", \"find duplication\", \"refactor candidates\", \"code quality scan\"\n- Stack-agnostic — leest project-config (stack, language, framework) en past per-stack heuristics toe\n- Output: markdown-rapport `docs/reviews/<datum>-<scope>-architecture-audit.md` met severity-getagde findings\n- **Geen code-fixes** — apart fix-traject (zie B)\n- 8 vaste dimensies (SOLID/DRY/YAGNI/naming/patterns/coupling/dead-code/a11y-of-equivalent)\n\n**B. `audit-fix` companion skill**\n- Reads audit-rapport, presenteert plan per finding (atomic commits)\n- User-approval-per-finding of batch\n- Schrijft code, niet rapport\n\n**C. Per-stack tuning-extension-points**\n- `audit-architecture-laravel` — Eloquent N+1, Policy-coverage, Service vs Action vs Job patroon, FormRequest-vs-controller-validation\n- `audit-architecture-react` — FSD-violations, props-bloat, god-components, hook-rules\n- `audit-architecture-go` — interface-bloat, package-cycles, error-wrapping consistency\n- Etc. — opt-in, ai-kit core blijft stack-agnostic\n\n## Quick win\n\nExisting `/audit` slash-skill (`description: \"Perform a full audit of the current code\"`) is te vaag. Eerste-stap-fix: vervang door beter-omschreven skill met expliciete 8 dimensies + rapport-output-pattern. Latere stap: per-stack extensions.\n\n## Refs\n\n- naschool-project-local: `~/.claude/projects/.../naschool/skills/frontend-audit/SKILL.md` (project-tuned, ~200 regels)\n- Sister-skill `frontend-audit` als reference-implementation voor stack-specific tuning\n- naschool sectie 3 sessie (2026-05-23): https://github.com/yusufkaracaburun/naschool/commit/bb332510","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/yusufkaracaburun/ai-kit/issues/32/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,