:0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"**Context:**\nIdentified during review of PR #239 (removal of `DefaultEmpty()`/`DefaultEmptyArray()` from `schema/pg`).\nReview thread: https://github.com/sofired/grizzle/pull/239#discussion_r3154532112\n\n> **Note (2026-04-29):** Project is in initial buildout with no existing users. The migration-compatibility concern in the original framing (existing snapshots with `'{}' ::jsonb` spacing) does not apply. This issue is a correctness improvement to the diff engine for future robustness.\n\n**Description:**\n`kit.Diff` compares `DefaultExpr` strings verbatim at `kit/diff.go:348`:\n\n```go\nif old.DefaultExpr != new.DefaultExpr || old.HasDefault != new.HasDefault {\n```\n\nThis means semantically-equivalent PostgreSQL default expressions that differ only in whitespace or cast formatting — for example `'{}' ::jsonb` vs `'{}'::jsonb` — will be treated as distinct values and generate a spurious `AlterColumnDefault` change, even though the resulting SQL is identical.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] `kit.Diff` normalizes `DefaultExpr` strings before comparison (at minimum: collapse whitespace around `::`, normalize cast spacing)\n- [ ] `AlterColumnDefault` is not emitted for expressions that are semantically equivalent under PostgreSQL's cast syntax rules\n- [ ] New tests added covering mixed-format cast expressions (e.g. JSONB, text, integer defaults)\n\n**Reference:**\n- Original PR: #239\n- Review thread: https://github.com/sofired/grizzle/pull/239#discussion_r3154532112","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sofired/grizzle/issues/241/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sofired/grizzle/issues/241/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Questi0nM4rk/shell-ast/issues/11","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Questi0nM4rk/shell-ast","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Questi0nM4rk/shell-ast/issues/11/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Questi0nM4rk/shell-ast/issues/11/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Questi0nM4rk/shell-ast/issues/11/events","html_url":"https://github.com/Questi0nM4rk/shell-ast/issues/11","id":4467730782,"node_id":"I_kwDORmdAPc8AAAABCkwpXg","number":11,"title":"Chained-wrapper unwrap: `sudo bash -c '...'` escapes one-level `unwrapCall` (BUG-008 follow-through)","user":{"login":"Questi0nM4rk","id":56120540,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjU2MTIwNTQw","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/56120540?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/Questi0nM4rk","html_url":"https://github.com/Questi0nM4rk","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Questi0nM4rk/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Questi0nM4rk/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Questi0nM4rk/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Questi0nM4rk/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Questi0nM4rk/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Questi0nM4rk/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Questi0nM4rk/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Questi0nM4rk/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Questi0nM4rk/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":6,"created_at":"2026-05-18T09:01:33Z","updated_at":"2026-05-18T10:26:18Z","closed_at":"2026-05-18T10:15:09Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"OWNER","active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"## Problem\n\n`unwrapCall` peels exactly one wrapper layer. For chained-wrapper invocations the inner command is unreachable from the primary lens, which fails IDEOLOGY §11 (\"primary lens must be complete\") for the natural security question *\"is this `rm` / `gcc` anywhere in the invocation chain?\"*\n\nConcrete case (already documented as BUG-008 in `docs/BUGS.md` since 2026-05-13, deferred from v0.4 and v0.6):\n\n```ts\nconst ast = await parse(\"sudo bash -c 'rm -rf /tmp/x'\");\nconst u = unwrapCall(findCalls(ast)[0]!);\n// u.kind === \"wrapped\"\n// u.wrapper === \"sudo\"\n// u.cmd === \"bash\"\n// u.flags === [\"-c\"]\n// u.args === [\"rm -rf /tmp/x\"]    ← the `-c` argument is opaque at this level\n```\n\nThe polymorphic query helpers added in 0.6.0 dispatch to `u.innerRaw` (the synthesized inner `bash -c '...'` call), so `tokensAfter(u, \"-c\")` finds the script string. But the *inner-inner* `rm -rf` is still unreachable — `bash -c` semantics mean the `-c` value IS a script, not a flag-value, and `unwrapCall` doesn't recognize the `wrapped` kind as a candidate for re-recursion the way it does for `wrapped-script`.\n\n## hook-kit consumer impact\n\nhook-kit pins this as a current limitation in `tests/builders/deep-nesting.test.ts` (committed in 0.6.0):\n\n```ts\ntest(\"sudo bash -c 'gcc -o /etc/passwd src.c' — sudo at outermost level (wrapped-opaque-then-recurse path)\", async () => {\n  // Today's known limitation (shell-ast BUG-008): sudo bash -c '…' unwraps\n  // as wrapped(sudo→bash) at the outer level; the bash -c argument is\n  // opaque to one-level unwrap. Our engine recursion fires only on\n  // kind=\"wrapped-script\", which `sudo bash -c '…'` is NOT (it's\n  // `wrapped`, the inner being bash). So the inner gcc currently escapes.\n  const mod = modOf(\n    cmd(\"gcc\")\n      .flagValueMatches(\"-o\", /^\\/(etc|sys|dev)/)\n      .deny(\"system path\"),\n  );\n  const out = await runModule({\n    module: mod,\n    command: 'sudo bash -c \"gcc -o /etc/passwd src.c\"',\n  });\n  expect(out.terminal).toBeNull(); // BUG-008 limitation — flip when shell-ast ships unwrapDeep\n});\n```\n\nThis is the kind of input that motivates hook-kit to exist: `sudo bash -c '<inner>'` is a textbook escalation pattern, and right now we can't catch the inner `rm` / `gcc` / etc. from the primary lens.\n\n## Suggested API (as documented in BUGS.md)\n\n```ts\nfunction unwrapDeep(call: CallExprNode, opts?: ResolveFlagsOptions): UnwrappedCall[];\n```\n\nReturns the unwrap chain, outermost first. For `sudo bash -c 'rm -rf /'` that's roughly:\n\n```ts\n[\n  { kind: \"wrapped\", wrapper: \"sudo\", cmd: \"bash\", ... },\n  { kind: \"wrapped-script\", wrapper: \"bash\", script: \"rm -rf /\", ... },\n  // and the consumer can parse the script with unwrapCallParsed for a\n  // third tier if they want symbolic-resolved deeper layers\n]\n```\n\nConsumer pattern becomes:\n\n```ts\nconst chain = unwrapDeep(call);\nfor (const layer of chain) {\n  switch (layer.kind) {\n    case \"plain\":\n    case \"wrapped\":\n      if (resolvedCmd(layer) === \"gcc\" && hasFlag(layer, \"-o\")) { ... }\n      break;\n    case \"wrapped-script\":\n      // inner is opaque source — consumer re-parses or uses unwrapCallParsed\n      break;\n    case \"wrapped-opaque\":\n      // wrapper-detected, inner dynamic — security signal preserved\n      break;\n  }\n}\n```\n\nhook-kit's engine recursion (`bash -c '…'` re-parse) already handles the `wrapped-script` case at the top level. What's missing is \"recurse on a `wrapped` whose inner is itself a wrapper-named command (like bash)\". `unwrapDeep` makes that one-step at the shell-ast layer instead of consumer-side state machine.\n\n## IDEOLOGY §11 framing\n\nThis is a primary-lens gap. The headline path (`parse → findCalls → unwrapCall → switch(u.kind)`) cannot answer *\"is this `gcc` anywhere in the invocation chain?\"* without falling through to either:\n\n1. **Consumer-side recursion on `u.cmd === \"bash\"` results** — hand-rolling chained-wrapper detection. Every consumer reinvents the wheel, with subtle differences in what counts as a wrapper (`bash`/`sh`/`dash`/`zsh`/`ksh`/`csh`/`tcsh`/`fish`/`env`/`time`/`exec`/`eval`/`nice`/`stdbuf`/…).\n2. **Parsing `u.args[0]` as a script when `u.cmd === \"bash\"`** — same as #1, just done by manually calling `parse` on the wrapper's `-c` argument. Re-implements the part of `unwrapCall` that already knows the `wrapped-script` shape, except entered from a `wrapped` lens.\n\nBoth paths are exactly what §11 says the escape hatch is NOT for. `unwrapDeep` (or an equivalent) collapses them into one primary-lens call.\n\n## Out of scope (per existing BUGS.md note)\n\n- Symbolic resolution of `wrapped-opaque` (e.g., `sudo $CMD`). The inner is unresolvable by definition.\n- Cycle detection (`bash -c \"bash -c '...'\"`) at infinite depth — depth limit lives at the consumer (hook-kit caps at 5).\n\n## hook-kit follow-through plan\n\nOnce `unwrapDeep` (or whatever shape shell-ast ships) lands:\n\n1. Bump hook-kit's dep to the new shell-ast minor.\n2. Add `unwrapDeep` usage in hook-kit's `engine/index.ts` inline-shell recursion path so wrapped-script-inside-wrapped is reached without the engine needing to re-parse the wrapper's script arg manually.\n3. Flip `tests/builders/deep-nesting.test.ts:50-70` from `expect(out.terminal).toBeNull()` to `expect(out.terminal?.kind).toBe(\"deny\")`.\n4. Remove the BUG-008-limitation comment in the same file.\n\nFiled during hook-kit autonomous-coding session 2026-05-18 after shell-ast agent reported no open issues. hook-kit 0.6/0.7 merged on main (commits 5afcf56 + 57df117); awaiting this unblock before npm publish.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Questi0nM4rk/shell-ast/issues/11/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Questi0nM4rk/shell-ast/issues/11/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/squne121/loop-protocol/issues/352","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/squne121/loop-protocol","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/squne121/loop-protocol/issues/352/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/squne121/loop-protocol/issues/352/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/squne121/loop-protocol/issues/352/events","html_url":"https://github.com/squne121/loop-protocol/issues/352","id":4510738530,"node_id":"I_kwDOSfQcDc8AAAABDNxoYg","number":352,"title":"調査: Spec Kit override/preset/extension の docs/ canonical 参照機構を機構別・template/command 別マトリクスと version 固定で文書化する（#334 後継）","user":{"login":"squne121","id":63350259,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjYzMzUwMjU5","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/63350259?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/squne121","html_url":"https://github.com/squne121","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/squne121/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/squne121/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/squne121/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/squne121/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/squne121/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/squne121/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/squne121/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/squne121/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/squne121/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[{"id":10997178698,"node_id":"LA_kwDOSfQcDc8AAAACj3uhSg","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/squne121/loop-protocol/labels/phase/research","name":"phase/research","color":"0075ca","default":false,"description":"Research phase issue"},{"id":10997178766,"node_id":"LA_kwDOSfQcDc8AAAACj3uhjg","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/squne121/loop-protocol/labels/agent/research","name":"agent/research","color":"e4e669","default":false,"description":"Handled by research agent"}],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":4,"created_at":"2026-05-24T06:40:16Z","updated_at":"2026-05-24T07:26:57Z","closed_at":"2026-05-24T07:26:57Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"OWNER","active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"## Machine-Readable Contract\n\n```yaml\ncontract_schema_version: v1\nissue_kind: research\nparent_issue: \"#283\"\nsupersedes: \"#334\"\ngoal_ref: \"Spec Kit の docs/ canonical 参照機構を、template resolution と command behavior を分離した二つのマトリクス、HOME/XDG 隔離 scratch 検証、spec-kit#2278 回帰確認、version 固定の検証証跡付きで調査し、ADR 0002 追補案または follow-up Implementation Issue 案を Allowed Paths 付きで提示する\"\nchange_kind: docs\nrevision: v2\n```\n\n## Parent Issue\n\n#283\n\n## Supersedes\n\n#334（同主旨の研究 Issue。AC が grep のみで成立し、Spec Kit の3機構を同列比較していたため close。本 Issue が後継）\n\n## Revision History\n\n- v1: 初版起票（#334 後継）\n- v2: 人間レビュー（#352 1st コメント）の BLOCKER 1–4 / MAJOR 1–4 を反映。`template resolution` と `command behavior / registration` の matrix 分離、scratch 検証の HOME/XDG 隔離、spec-kit#2278 回帰確認の AC 昇格、extension の独立カテゴリ化、`.specify/memory/constitution.md` Recommended default の事前固定、`tested_spec_kit` への `install_method` 追加、#335/#348 merged 状態への非重複追記、`command overrides / hooks` 用語の分解\n\n## Outcome\n\n`docs/dev/spec-kit-override-investigation.md` が作成され、以下のすべてを満たした状態:\n\n1. `tested_spec_kit` ブロック（`specify_cli_version` / `source_tag_or_commit` / `install_method` / `checked_at` / `integration`）が記載されている\n2. **二つに分離された** マトリクスが存在する:\n   - **Template resolution matrix**（spec-template / plan-template / tasks-template / constitution-template × project-local overrides / preset / extension）\n   - **Command behavior / registration matrix**（`/constitution` / `/specify` / `/plan` / `/tasks` / `/taskstoissues` / `/implement` × runtime override 可否 / install-time registration 仕様 / hook 呼び出し点）\n3. extension が独立カテゴリとして扱われ、「override 手段の下位互換」ではなく「新 command / hook / quality gate / 外部連携の配布手段」として記述されている\n4. `.specify/memory/constitution.md` の取り扱いは **「derived pointer として維持」を Recommended default とし**、完全排除案は alternative として記載される（理由: Spec Kit constitution command が当該ファイルを更新対象として明示しているため）\n5. scratch 検証は HOME / XDG_CONFIG_HOME を隔離した状態で行われ、その隔離手順と `env | rg 'HOME|XDG|SPECKIT'` summary が文書に記録されている\n6. spec-kit#2278 の回帰確認（`tasks-template` について `setup-tasks.sh` の `resolve_template \"tasks-template\"` 呼び出しと `tasks.md` の `TASKS_TEMPLATE` 消費）が証跡化されている\n7. ADR 0002 への追補要否と、必要であれば follow-up Implementation Issue 案（Allowed Paths / Stop Conditions 付き）が記載されている\n8. 既存 follow-up（#332 / #335→#348 / #338）との非重複セクションが、#348 merged 状態を反映して記載されている\n\n## In Scope\n\n- Spec Kit 公式 docs（presets / extensions / templates / commands / scripts）の一次情報収集（tag 固定 URL）\n- 5機構（project-local template overrides / preset-provided files / extension-provided files / extension hooks / installed command registration / command snapshot overrides）の概念整理\n- Template resolution matrix と Command behavior / registration matrix の **個別** 作成\n- `.specify/memory/constitution.md` の取り扱い: derived pointer 維持を default として記述、完全排除案は alternative\n- HOME/XDG 隔離 scratch project（`/tmp/loop-speckit-override-investigation-*` および `/tmp/loop-speckit-home-*` / `/tmp/loop-speckit-xdg-*`）での挙動確認\n- spec-kit#2278 の回帰確認\n- 推奨アプローチ（short-term / medium-term / avoid）と follow-up decision\n- `docs/dev/spec-kit-override-investigation.md` の作成\n\n## Out of Scope\n\n- Spec Kit 実設定の永続変更（`.specify/` / `.claude/skills/` / `.claude/commands/` への commit）\n- 開発者環境（`~/.specify`、installed agent command directories）への mutation\n- ADR の新規追加・本文更新（追補案の提示のみ可。実反映は別 Issue）\n- CI / ビルド設定の変更\n- #332 / #335→#348 / #338 の責務領域（routing gate / Product Spec Preflight (PS001–PS006) / trace 構造チェック）への手出し・再定義\n\n## Required Investigation Matrix\n\n`docs/dev/spec-kit-override-investigation.md` は最低限以下のセクションを含むこと:\n\n### 1. Version / environment\n\n```yaml\ntested_spec_kit:\n  specify_cli_version: \"<output of `specify --version`>\"\n  source_tag_or_commit: \"v0.8.13 / <sha>\"\n  install_method: \"uv tool install ... / local checkout / git+https / etc.\"\n  checked_at: \"YYYY-MM-DD\"\n  integration: \"codex skills / claude commands / other\"\ndocs_reference:\n  base_url: \"https://github.com/github/spec-kit/blob/<tag>/\"\n  note: \"docs は CLI と同じ tag に固定する\"\n```\n\n### 2. Mechanism comparison（5 機構）\n\n| Mechanism | Purpose | Resolution timing | Write targets | Upgrade risk | LOOP compatibility |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| project-local template overrides | repo 内 template 差し替え | runtime | `.specify/templates/overrides/` | low | high |\n| preset-provided files | 複数 repo への template / command / terminology 配布 | template=runtime / command=install-time | preset catalog + agent dirs | medium | conditional |\n| extension-provided files | 新 command / template / 外部連携配布 | install-time | `.specify/extensions/<ext>/` + agent dirs | high | low（canonical docs 目的には過剰）|\n| extension hooks | `.specify/extensions.yml` の `hooks.before_*` / `hooks.after_*` 呼び出し | runtime（command 実行中） | hook script | medium | conditional |\n| installed command registration / command snapshot overrides | agent integration（`.claude/skills/`, `.claude/commands/`）への登録・差し替え | install-time | `.claude/skills/`, `.claude/commands/` | very high（reviewed snapshot 方針と衝突） | low |\n\n### 3-A. Template resolution matrix\n\n| Template | project-local overrides | preset | extension | Evidence |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| `spec-template` | | | | `resolve_template \"spec-template\"` transcript / docs ref |\n| `plan-template` | | | | |\n| `tasks-template` | | | | spec-kit#2278 回帰確認結果を含む |\n| `constitution-template` | | | | |\n\nEvidence は (a) 公式 docs の tag 固定 URL の該当行、または (b) HOME/XDG 隔離 scratch project での `resolve_template` / `specify preset resolve` の transcript 要約。\n\n### 3-B. Command behavior / registration matrix\n\n| Command | install-time registration の挙動 | runtime override 可否 | hook 呼び出し点 | Evidence |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| `/constitution` | | | `hooks.before_constitution` / `hooks.after_constitution` | command file source ref |\n| `/specify` | | | | |\n| `/plan` | | | | |\n| `/tasks` | | | `hooks.before_tasks` / `hooks.after_tasks` | |\n| `/taskstoissues` | | | | |\n| `/implement` | | | | |\n\n**注意:** template resolution の結果から command behavior を推論しない。各 command は command file source または agent registration の挙動から個別に判定する。\n\n### 4. Docs canonical boundary analysis\n\n- `.specify/memory/constitution.md` を **derived pointer として維持** する場合の pointer 本文骨子（参照すべき docs: `docs/adr/0002-sdd-tool-adoption.md` / `docs/dev/product-spec-lifecycle.md` / `docs/product/**`）\n- 完全排除案を採用した場合に Spec Kit constitution command がどう壊れるか / 回避策の有無\n- `docs/` と `.specify/memory/constitution.md` の conflict 解消方法\n- ADR 0002 の `docs/` normative 原則との整合性\n\n### 5. Recommended approach\n\nshort-term / medium-term / avoid を明示し、各推奨に「なぜそれを選ぶか」の根拠（一次情報 ref）を記載。\n\n### 6. Follow-up decision\n\n以下のいずれかを具体的に提示:\n- ADR 0002 追補案（追記すべきセクション骨子）\n- follow-up Implementation Issue 案（Outcome / Allowed Paths / Stop Conditions / VC 骨子付き）\n\n### 7. Non-overlap with existing follow-ups\n\n```md\n- #332: routing signal only; この調査は data-plane 手順をそこに追加してはならない\n- #335 / #348 (merged): Product Spec Preflight は既に merged。本調査は PS001–PS006 を既存 guardrail として引用するに留め、**意味論を再定義したり checker logic を duplicate する follow-up を出してはならない**\n- #338: trace field structure check; 本調査は必須 trace fields を参照するのみ\n- future adapter issue: Spec Kit override/preset/extension の実装が必要な場合のみ起票\n```\n\n### 8. Scratch verification environment isolation\n\nscratch 検証は以下を満たすこと:\n\n```bash\nexport HOME=\"/tmp/loop-speckit-home-$(date +%s)\"\nexport XDG_CONFIG_HOME=\"/tmp/loop-speckit-xdg-$(date +%s)\"\nmkdir -p \"$HOME\" \"$XDG_CONFIG_HOME\"\n#