 / LOOP_STATE.product_spec_context 更新 / worker routing のみを行い、成果物手順を含まない\"\nchange_kind: workflow\n```\n\n## Parent Issue\n\n#283\n\n## Parent Goal Ref\n\n- Goal: SDD ライフサイクル定義（docs/dev/product-spec-lifecycle.md）を整備し、Spec Kit / product spec の運用境界を明確化する\n- Desired Destination: issue-refinement-loop を含む AI ワークフローが product spec phase を認識し、適切な routing gate を経由して worker skill へ処理を委譲できる状態\n\n## Current Validated Scope\n\n- `.claude/skills/issue-refinement-loop/SKILL.md` に Product/Spec Kit signal detection と routing gate のみを追加する\n- gate は signal detection / LOOP_STATE.product_spec_context 更新 / worker routing のみを行い、成果物手順を含まない\n- `LOOP_STATE.product_spec_context` フィールドを追加する（signal detected flag + work_kind metadata）\n- `docs/product/**` / `.specify/**` / `spec.md` / `plan.md` / `tasks.md` / `speckit` / `Spec Kit` 検知時に、後続 worker へ opaque context を渡す\n- `tasks.md` 直接実装要求を検知した場合は implementation へ進めず、Issue materialization 経路へ route する（fail-closed）\n- 成果物作成・更新・archive・trace fields 具体手順は issue-refinement-loop へ書かない\n\n## Remaining Parent Gaps\n\n- `review-issue/SKILL.md` 側への Product Spec 対応（必要と判明した場合は別 Issue）\n- docs/dev/product-spec-lifecycle.md 本体の実装（#283 本体）\n- follow-up Issue: `review-issue` / `issue-contract-review` / `impl-review-loop` / `speckit-taskstoissues` への成果物手順・preflight の分割\n\n## Background\n\nPR #322（https://github.com/squne121/loop-protocol/pull/322#issuecomment-4527033128）の人間レビューで「後続 Issue A」として提案された。当初は全 preflight を issue-refinement-loop に統合する設計だったが、ORCHESTRATOR_IO_BOUNDARY_V1（control-plane/data-plane 分離原則）に反するとして OWNER より REQUEST_CHANGES 相当の設計変更要求を受けた。正しいアプローチは「薄い routing gate のみ issue-refinement-loop に追加、詳細手順は SubAgent/worker skill に分割」。親 Issue は #283（SDD ライフサイクル定義）および #254（SDD 駆動運用方針）。\n\n## Outcome\n\n`.claude/skills/issue-refinement-loop/SKILL.md` に Product/Spec Kit signal detection と routing gate が追加された状態で、gate は signal detection / LOOP_STATE.product_spec_context 更新 / worker routing のみを行い、成果物手順を含まない。pnpm typecheck && pnpm lint && pnpm test && pnpm build が PASS している。\n\n## In Scope\n\n- `.claude/skills/issue-refinement-loop/SKILL.md` に Product/Spec Kit signal detection と routing gate のみ追加する\n- `LOOP_STATE.product_spec_context` フィールドを追加する（signal detected flag + work_kind metadata）\n- `docs/product/**` / `.specify/**` / `spec.md` / `plan.md` / `tasks.md` / `speckit` / `Spec Kit` 検知時に、後続 worker へ opaque context を渡す\n- `tasks.md` 直接実装要求を検知した場合は implementation route に進まず、Issue materialization 経路へ route する（fail-closed）\n- 成果物作成・更新・archive・trace fields 具体手順は issue-refinement-loop へ書かない\n- 必要な follow-up Issue を記録する（起票または既存 Issue 参照）:\n  - `review-issue` / `issue-reviewer`: product trace fields の構造チェック追加\n  - `issue-contract-review`: product/spec-kit implementation preflight\n  - `impl-review-loop` / `implementation-worker`: tasks.md / speckit-implement direct execution guard\n  - `speckit-taskstoissues`: LOOP_PROTOCOL adapter alignment\n\n## Out of Scope\n\n- Product spec 本文の作成手順\n- docs/product/** の frontmatter / EARS / archive 手順の詳細\n- tasks.md → GitHub Issue 変換アルゴリズム\n- speckit-* upstream 手順の再定義\n- trace fields（product_spec_id / requirement_id / source_task_id）の詳細要求手順\n- phase 分類の詳細作業手順（routing enum としての記述は可）\n- `issue-refinement-loop` から worker skill を直接実行する設計\n- 新規 skill ファイルの作成\n- `review-issue/SKILL.md` の変更（必要な場合は別 Issue）\n- `docs/product/**` 配下のファイル自体の変更\n- `.specify/` workbench ファイルの変更\n- UI / src / tests の変更\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] AC1: `issue-refinement-loop/SKILL.md` に Product/Spec Kit routing gate セクションが追加されている\n- [ ] AC2: gate は signal detection / LOOP_STATE.product_spec_context 更新 / worker routing のみを行い、成果物手順を含まない（grep で「phase 分類の詳細手順」「trace fields の要求手順」「tasks.md → GitHub Issue 化」に相当するテキストが存在しないこと）\n- [ ] AC3: `tasks.md` 直接実装要求を検知した場合は implementation route に進まず、Issue materialization route へ振り分けられる記述がある\n- [ ] AC4: `review-issue` / `issue-contract-review` / `impl-review-loop` / `speckit-taskstoissues` への follow-up Issue が起票または既存 Issue として本文に参照されている\n- [ ] AC5: `issue-refinement-loop/SKILL.md` に `docs/product/**` frontmatter、EARS、registry template、Spec Kit command の詳細手順が追加されていない\n- [ ] AC6: #203 / #295 との同一ファイル競合リスクが `## Delivery Rule` に明示されている\n\n## Verification Commands\n\n```bash\n# AC1: routing gate セクションの存在確認\ngrep -n \"routing gate\\|routing_gate\\|product_spec_context\\|Product.*Spec.*Routing\\|Spec Kit.*routing\" .claude/skills/issue-refinement-loop/SKILL.md && echo \"PASS: routing gate section found\" || echo \"FAIL: routing gate section not found\"\n\n# AC2: 成果物手順が含まれないことの確認\n! grep -n \"phase 分類の詳細\\|trace field.*要求\\|tasks.md.*GitHub Issue 化\\|docs\\/product.*frontmatter\\|EARS\\|registry template\" .claude/skills/issue-refinement-loop/SKILL.md && echo \"PASS: no data-plane procedures\" || echo \"FAIL: data-plane procedures found\"\n\n# AC3: tasks.md fail-closed の記述確認\ngrep -n \"tasks.md.*direct\\|tasks.md.*禁止\\|tasks.md.*materialization\\|fail.closed.*tasks\" .claude/skills/issue-refinement-loop/SKILL.md && echo \"PASS: tasks.md guard found\" || echo \"FAIL: tasks.md guard missing\"\n\n# AC4: follow-up Issue 参照の確認\ngrep -n \"issue-contract-review\\|impl-review-loop\\|speckit-taskstoissues\" .claude/skills/issue-refinement-loop/SKILL.md && echo \"PASS: follow-up references found\" || echo \"FAIL: follow-up references missing\"\n\n# AC5: 詳細手順が追加されていないことの確認\n! grep -n \"specify init\\|speckit.tasks generates\\|/speckit\\.implement\" .claude/skills/issue-refinement-loop/SKILL.md && echo \"PASS: no speckit upstream procedures\" || echo \"FAIL: speckit upstream procedures found\"\n\n# AC6: 品質ゲート\npnpm typecheck && pnpm lint && pnpm test && pnpm build\n```\n\n## Allowed Paths\n\n- `.claude/skills/issue-refinement-loop/SKILL.md`\n\n## Stop Conditions\n\n- Allowed Paths 外の変更が必要と判明した場合\n- In Scope の固定契約（キー集合・スキーマ・型定義）の変更が必要になった場合\n- 新規 Issue の起票が必要と判断した場合（スコープ分割が発生する場合）\n- 後続 Phase / 別スコープへの波及が判明した場合\n- nested SubAgent delegation が必要になった場合\n- 外部サービス利用・権限昇格・既存テスト大規模改変が必要になった場合\n- tasks.md の直接実装が必要と思われる場合（tasks.md materialization 規約: 直接実装禁止、必ず sub-issue 経由）\n\n## Required Skills\n\nなし\n\n## Runtime Verification Applicability\n\n```yaml\nruntime_verification_applicability:\n  decision: immediate\n  rationale: >\n    SKILL.md へのテキスト追加であり、grep ベースの VC が即時実行可能。\n    pnpm typecheck / lint / test / build は CI で常時実行される。\n    AC2/AC3/AC5 は否定的 grep（存在しないこと）で baseline FAIL が確認可能。\n  verification_commands_ref: AC1-AC6\n```\n<!-- runtime-verification: true -->\n\n## Scope Delta（任意）\n\nreframe: 設計変更要求（OWNER REQUEST_CHANGES 相当）により、全 preflight 統合から薄い routing gate のみへ縮小。詳細手順は worker skill へ分割。\n\n## Delivery Rule\n\n- `1 Issue = 1 PR`\n- 同一ファイル（`issue-refinement-loop/SKILL.md`）を変更する #203 / #295 が OPEN のため、それらとマージコンフリクトが生じないよう直列で処理することを推奨する\n\n## Source\n\n- dedupe_key: spec-kit-loop-integration:A\n- source_pr: https://github.com/squne121/loop-protocol/pull/322#issuecomment-4527033128\n- proposed_as: 後続 Issue A（PR #322 人間レビュー）\n","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/squne121/loop-protocol/issues/332/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/squne121/loop-protocol/issues/332/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/darrylmorley/whatcable/issues/155","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/darrylmorley/whatcable","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/darrylmorley/whatcable/issues/155/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/darrylmorley/whatcable/issues/155/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/darrylmorley/whatcable/issues/155/events","html_url":"https://github.com/darrylmorley/whatcable/issues/155","id":4464923278,"node_id":"I_kwDOSRenPs8AAAABCiFSjg","number":155,"title":"[Bug] CLI --test-kit finds no probes and submits nothing; also needs a consent prompt","user":{"login":"darrylmorley","id":20406137,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjIwNDA2MTM3","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/20406137?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/darrylmorley","html_url":"https://github.com/darrylmorley","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/darrylmorley/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/darrylmorley/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/darrylmorley/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/darrylmorley/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/darrylmorley/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/darrylmorley/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/darrylmorley/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/darrylmorley/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/darrylmorley/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[{"id":10836466638,"node_id":"LA_kwDOSRenPs8AAAAChedbzg","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/darrylmorley/whatcable/labels/bug","name":"bug","color":"d73a4a","default":true,"description":"Something isn't working"}],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":2,"created_at":"2026-05-17T21:02:12Z","updated_at":"2026-05-18T12:45:24Z","closed_at":"2026-05-17T22:50:37Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"OWNER","active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"### What\n\n`whatcable --test-kit` (v0.11.0) reports every bundled probe as \"skipped (not found)\" and submits 0 probes. The CLI test kit does nothing.\n\n```\nWhatCable Test Kit v0.11.0\nRunning 13 diagnostic probes...\n\n  [1/13] 01_walk_pd_tree... skipped (not found)\n  [2/13] 03_hpm_deep_dive... skipped (not found)\n  [3/13] 04_raw_registry_dump... skipped (not found)\n  [4/13] 16_transient_props... skipped (not found)\n  [5/13] 17_deep_property_dump... skipped (not found)\n  [6/13] 19_pdo_decode_and_usb3_watch... skipped (not found)\n  [7/13] 21_tb_cfplugin_retimer... skipped (not found)\n  [8/13] 25_usb_bos_descriptor... skipped (not found)\n  [9/13] 26_displayport_altmode... skipped (not found)\n  [10/13] 27_iopower_management... skipped (not found)\n  [11/13] 29_usb4_router_interfaces... skipped (not found)\n  [12/13] 31_typec_phy_properties... skipped (not found)\n  [13/13] 32_smart_battery_full_keys... skipped (not found)\n\nDone: 0 probes submitted. Thanks for contributing!\n```\n\n### Why it happens\n\nThe CLI locates the bundled probe binaries relative to the app bundle's resources. When `whatcable` runs as the CLI (from PATH / `WhatCable.app/Contents/Helpers/whatcable`) rather than as the GUI app, that lookup does not resolve to `Contents/Resources/probes`, so none of the 13 probes are found. The GUI \"Contribute Diagnostic Data\" path uses a different resolver and appears unaffected.\n\n### Impact\n\nThe CLI test kit is non-functional: 0 probes run, nothing submitted. Anyone following CLI instructions to contribute diagnostics gets nothing back.\n\n### Also needed: explicit consent in the CLI\n\n`--test-kit` currently runs the probes and submits to a remote endpoint with no interactive confirmation. Before running or sending anything it should show a y/n prompt that clearly states what is collected and where it goes, and proceed only on an explicit \"y\". The GUI path is an opt-in button; the CLI should be equivalently explicit.\n\n### Proposed fix\n\n- Resolve the probes directory robustly when running as the CLI (find `Contents/Resources/probes` relative to the executable inside the `.app`, not via the GUI-only main-bundle resource lookup).\n- Add a y/n consent prompt to `--test-kit` that discloses the collected data and the destination before any probe runs or data is sent.\n\n### Repro\n\n1. Install via Homebrew (or use the bundled CLI).\n2. Run `whatcable --test-kit`.\n3. Observed: all 13 probes \"skipped (not found)\", \"Done: 0 probes submitted.\"\n","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/darrylmorley/whatcable/issues/155/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/darrylmorley/whatcable/issues/155/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/github/spec-kit/issues/2624","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/github/spec-kit","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/github/spec-kit/issues/2624/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/github/spec-kit/issues/2624/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/github/spec-kit/issues/2624/events","html_url":"https://github.com/github/spec-kit/issues/2624","id":4473764695,"node_id":"I_kwDOPiFCnc8AAAABCqg7Vw","number":2624,"title":"[Extension]: Update Agent Governance to v1.2.0","user":{"login":"bigsmartben","id":30429295,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjMwNDI5Mjk1","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/30429295?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/bigsmartben","html_url":"https://github.com/bigsmartben","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bigsmartben/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bigsmartben/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bigsmartben/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bigsmartben/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bigsmartben/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bigsmartben/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bigsmartben/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bigsmartben/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bigsmartben/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":2,"created_at":"2026-05-19T01:40:04Z","updated_at":"2026-05-21T13:09:08Z","closed_at":"2026-05-21T13:08:49Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"NONE","issue_field_values":[],"type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"This is an update to the existing `agent-governance` community catalog entry. The extension is already listed in `extensions/catalog.community.json`; this submission updates the version, download URL, description, required tool metadata, and behavior summary for v1.2.0.\n\nRelated previous submissions: #2552, #2569.\n\n## Extension ID\n\nagent-governance\n\n## Extension Name\n\nAgent Governance\n\n## Version\n\n1.2.0\n\n## Description\n\nGenerate agent-platform repository governance files from Spec Kit metadata.\n\n## Author\n\nbigben\n\n## Repository URL\n\nhttps://github.com/bigsmartben/spec-kit-agent-governance\n\n## Download URL\n\nhttps://github.com/bigsmartben/spec-kit-agent-governance/archive/refs/tags/v1.2.0.zip\n\n## License\n\nMIT\n\n## Homepage\n\nhttps://github.com/bigsmartben/spec-kit-agent-governance\n\n## Documentation URL\n\nhttps://github.com/bigsmartben/spec-kit-agent-governance/blob/main/README.md\n\n## Changelog URL\n\nhttps://github.com/bigsmartben/spec-kit-agent-governance/blob/main/CHANGELOG.md\n\n## Required Spec Kit Version\n\n>=0.8.0\n\n## Required Tools\n\n- uv - required\n\n## Number of Commands\n\n1\n\n## Number of Hooks\n\n3\n\n## Tags\n\ngovernance, agents, memory, context\n\n## Key Features\n\n- Generate or update the active agent platform governance file from Spec Kit integration metadata.\n- Initialize the internal governance cache from detected repository evidence and manifest-backed commands.\n- Preserve user-authored content outside managed `SPECKIT GOVERNANCE` markers.\n- Use the active managed section as the refresh source for reviewed governance changes.\n- Distill repository areas into concise action rules with depth limited to two directory levels, including hidden and cache directories.\n- Clean stale managed sections from known non-active agent context files.\n- Keep project-governance ownership external to this extension.\n\n## Testing Checklist\n\n- [x] Extension installs successfully via download URL\n- [x] All commands execute without errors\n- [x] Documentation is complete and accurate\n- [x] No security vulnerabilities identified\n- [x] Tested on at least one real project\n\n## Submission Requirements\n\n- [x] Valid `extension.yml` manifest included\n- [x] README.md with installation and usage instructions\n- [x] LICENSE file included\n- [x] GitHub release created with version tag\n- [x] All command files exist and are properly formatted\n- [x] Extension ID follows naming conventions (lowercase-with-hyphens)\n\n## Testing Details\n\n**Tested on:**\n- macOS with Spec Kit `specify 0.8.11`\n- Repository test suite using `uv`\n\n**Commands run:**\n- `uv run python -m py_compile scripts/refresh_agent_governance.py tests/test_governance_domains.py`\n- `uv run pytest -q` (`22 passed`)\n- `git diff --check`\n- `specify extension add agent-governance --from https://github.com/bigsmartben/spec-kit-agent-governance/archive/refs/tags/v1.2.0.zip`\n- In a temporary Spec Kit project, installed from the v1.2.0 release archive and ran `uv run python .specify/extensions/agent-governance/scripts/refresh_agent_governance.py`; it generated/updated `AGENTS.md` successfully.\n\n**Release:**\n- https://github.com/bigsmartben/spec-kit-agent-governance/releases/tag/v1.2.0\n\n## Example Usage\n\n```bash\nspecify extension add agent-governance --from https://github.com/bigsmartben/spec-kit-agent-governance/archive/refs/tags/v1.2.0.zip\n\n/speckit.agent-governance.refresh\n```\n\n## Proposed Catalog Entry\n\n```json\n{\n  \"agent-governance\": {\n    \"name\": \"Agent Governance\",\n    \"id\": \"agent-governance\",\n    \"description\": \"Generate agent-platform repository governance files from Spec Kit metadata.\",\n    \"author\": \"bigben\",\n    \"version\": \"1.2.0\",\n    \"download_url\": \"https://github.com/bigsmartben/spec-kit-agent-governance/archive/refs/tags/v1.2.0.zip\",\n    \"repository\": \"https://github.com/bigsmartben/spec-kit-agent-governance\",\n    \"homepage\": \"https://github.com/bigsmartben/spec-kit-agent-governance\",\n    \"documentation\": \"https://github.com/bigsmartben/spec-kit-agent-governance/blob/main/README.md\",\n    \"changelog\": \"https://github.com/bigsmartben/spec-kit-agent-governance/blob/main/CHANGELOG.md\",\n    \"license\": \"MIT\",\n    \"requires\": {\n      \"speckit_version\": \">=0.8.0\",\n      \"tools\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"uv\",\n          \"required\": true\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    \"provides\": {\n      \"commands\": 1,\n      \"hooks\": 3\n    },\n    \"tags\": [\n      \"governance\",\n      \"agents\",\n      \"memory\",\n      \"context\"\n    ],\n    \"verified\": false,\n    \"downloads\": 0,\n    \"stars\": 0,\n    \"created_at\": \"2026-03-31T00:00:00Z\",\n    \"updated_at\": \"2026-05-19T00:00:00Z\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n## Additional Context\n\nThis v1.2.0 update changes the extension from a memory-file-centered projection to an active managed-section SSOT flow. It also updates the required runtime tool from optional `python3` to required `uv`, matching the command and validation workflow.\n","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/github/spec-kit/issues/2624/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/github/spec-kit/issues/2624/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/niznik-dev/cruijff_kit/issues/503","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos