_radar_by_task`, `scores_radar_by_task_df`) **do exist** in v0.3.4 — they live under `inspect_viz.view.beta`, not `inspect_viz.view`. The top-level `inspect_viz.view` module is empty:\n\n```python\n>>> import inspect_viz.view, inspect_viz.view.beta\n>>> [x for x in dir(inspect_viz.view) if not x.startswith('_')]\n[]\n>>> [x for x in dir(inspect_viz.view.beta) if not x.startswith('_')][:6]\n['scores_by_factor', 'scores_by_limit', 'scores_by_model', 'scores_by_task', 'scores_heatmap', 'scores_radar_by_task']\n```\n\nThe `beta` namespace appears to signal that the upstream API is still evolving — these functions used to be at `inspect_viz.view` and may eventually return there, but right now they don't.\n\n## Where the skill references them\n\nAll in `.claude/skills/analyze-experiment/`:\n\n- `generation.md` line 19–26: top-of-file import block uses `from inspect_viz.view import ...`\n- `SKILL.md` lines 62–66, 140–146, 165–173, 271–273: textual references\n- `logging.md` lines 84, 86, 88: example log entries\n\n`pyproject.toml` declares `\"inspect-viz\"` unpinned, so users get whatever's current on PyPI. As of v0.3.4 the docs are broken.\n\n## Steps to Reproduce\n\n1. Install or update cruijff_kit deps in any reasonably current environment (`inspect_viz==0.3.4`).\n2. Run `analyze-experiment` on any experiment.\n3. First call into `inspect_viz.view` imports raises `ImportError`.\n\n## Workaround used in the COLING-cue experiment\n\nSkipped the inspect-viz views entirely and produced all charts with matplotlib (bar charts + imshow heatmaps). The per-sample helpers in `viz_helpers.py` (`generate_roc_overlay`, `generate_calibration_overlay`, `generate_prediction_histogram`) are matplotlib-based and worked fine.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Update import paths in `.claude/skills/analyze-experiment/generation.md` (and all references in `SKILL.md`, `logging.md`) to `from inspect_viz.view.beta import ...` for v0.3.4.\n- [ ] Pin `inspect-viz` to a known-tested range in `pyproject.toml` (e.g. `inspect-viz>=0.3.4,<0.4` if the `.beta` location is stable in this minor; or to the most recent version where `inspect_viz.view` did expose these names if a stable version is preferred).\n- [ ] Add a guard / friendly error: if the import fails, point at the docs/pin rather than just propagating `ImportError`. Could live in `viz_helpers.py` as a `try_import_views()` helper.\n- [ ] Track upstream: when `inspect_viz.view.beta.scores_*` graduate to `inspect_viz.view`, flip back; for now, leaving comment in `generation.md` noting why `.beta` is used.\n\n## Related\n\nSurfaced while running `analyze-experiment` on the experiment that produced #498.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/niznik-dev/cruijff_kit/issues/503/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/niznik-dev/cruijff_kit/issues/503/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/community-scripts/ProxmoxVE/issues/14551","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/community-scripts/ProxmoxVE","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/community-scripts/ProxmoxVE/issues/14551/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/community-scripts/ProxmoxVE/issues/14551/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/community-scripts/ProxmoxVE/issues/14551/events","html_url":"https://github.com/community-scripts/ProxmoxVE/issues/14551","id":4465286488,"node_id":"I_kwDONJEens8AAAABCibdWA","number":14551,"title":"[Profilarr] Unable to create Profilarr LXC from community-scripts after Profilarr updated to v2.0","user":{"login":"asiananimal","id":185639673,"node_id":"U_kgDOCxCi-Q","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/185639673?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/asiananimal","html_url":"https://github.com/asiananimal","followers_url"